14 MAY: The BBC visits an English school which has introduced a buddy bus stop sign in the playground, to help children who feel sad or find themselves on their own at break time. Children who want a friend go and stand by the sign, and if other children see them there, they invite them to play with them. This idea is being used in schools across the country.
